tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE 3d_printing_designs (
    design_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    design_name VARCHAR(50),
    designer_name VARCHAR(50),
    material_used VARCHAR(50),
    file_path VARCHAR(100)
);

CREATE TABLE specifications (
    spec_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    design_id INT REFERENCES designs(design_id),
    filament_type TEXT,
    print_speed INT,
    layer_height REAL
);

CREATE TABLE specifications (
   id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
   design_id INT NOT NULL,
   material VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
   layer_thickness INT NOT NULL,
   print_speed INT NOT NULL,
   FOREIGN KEY (design_id) REFERENCES designs(id)
);

CREATE TABLE Design (
 id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 name VARCHAR(255),
 designer VARCHAR(255),
 size DECIMAL,
 material VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE Printer (
 id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 brand VARCHAR(255),
 model VARCHAR(255),
 type VARCHAR(255),
 size VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE PrintJob (
 id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 design_id INT,
 printer_id INT,
 start_time TIMESTAMP,
 end_time TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE Material (
 id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 name VARCHAR(255),
 type VARCHAR(255),
 color VARCHAR(255),
 price DECIMAL
)

CREATE TABLE User (
 id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 username VARCHAR(255),
 email VARCHAR(255),
 role VARCHAR(255),
 last_login TIMESTAMP
)
